Debian - Debian/ubuntu/Kali/Raspberry   -->apt is app store. 
rhel(enterprise)/centos/oel(ent)  --> yum 
fedora  --> dnf 


epel repo --> this is a geneirc repo for rhel/centos/oel 

Every APp store is a configurataion file. --> /etc 

you can create a local yum. 

**Debian COmmands 
apt upgrade or apt-get upgrade 
apt full-upgrade or apt-get dist-upgrade
apt install <pkg-name> 
apt -y install <pkg-name>
apt remove <pkg-name>
apt-cache search <pkg-name> - give the pkg and description
apt-cache showpkg <pkg-name> - list dependencies 
apt-cache show <pkg-name> - show pkg info. 
apt-get clean (clean the .deb files downloaded)
apt-get download <pkg-name> - download witout install


**RHEL 

yum install <pkg-name>
yum -y install <pkg-name>
yum -y groupinstall <group-name>
yum search <pkg-name>
yum -v repolist 
yum remove <pkg-name>
yum reinstall <pkg-name>
yum info <pkg-name>
yum clean all  --> Clean Yum Cache
yum -y localinstall * --> install rpm files as yum. 


Note:- 
1. Every COnnection has a Port Number 
    <1024 --> owned by root , [sudo , stickybit has to be used if it has to start with anathor user.]
    >1024 - 9999 --> statuc Ports 
    9999 - 65535 --> dynamic ports. 

  important protocols and port numbers in linux. --> https://hostingreviewbox.com/rhel-tcp-and-udp-ports/

